name: Candi Jolotundo
address: Area Hutan, Hutan, Kec. Trawas, Kabupaten Mojokerto, Jawa Timur 61375
description: Candi Jolotundo is an ancient temple complex located in Trowulan, East Java, Indonesia. It is believed to have been built during the Majapahit Empire, which existed from the 13th to the 15th century. The complex consists of three temples, and is one of the few remaining Hindu temples from the Majapahit period that are still preserved in relatively good condition. The temple is built of red brick and has a typical structure of Hindu temple in Java, with its three parts representing Trimurti (the Hindu Triad), the base, the body and the pinnacle. It is also known for its intricate carvings, that can be found all over the temple, depicting scenes from Hindu epics and mythology. The temple complex is considered a valuable historical and cultural site, and is a popular destination for tourists and history enthusiasts. it is open for the public to visit and it is one of the main attraction in Trowulan. Candi Jolotundo is also considered as an important site to study about ancient Javanese Hindu Architecture, as it gives a glimpse of how grandeur the architecture in Majapahit era.

name: Museum Majapahit Trowulan

description: The Museum Majapahit Trowulan, also known as the Trowulan Museum, is a museum located in Trowulan, East Java, Indonesia. Trowulan is the site of the capital of the 14th-century Majapahit Empire, one of the largest and most powerful empires in Southeast Asian history. The museum houses a collection of artifacts and ruins from the Majapahit Empire, including ceramics, stone sculptures, and architectural fragments. The artifacts on display are from the excavations in the Trowulan archaeological site and surrounding area. The exhibits are divided into several halls, including a hall displaying statues and stone reliefs, a hall showcasing ceramics, a hall displaying architectural remains, and a hall dedicated to the history of the Majapahit Empire. Additionally, the museum also provides education about the Majapahit civilization for visitor, it gives a detailed history about the civilization, its society and way of living. It is a popular destination for history and culture enthusiasts, as well as for those interested in the archaeology of ancient Southeast Asia.

description: Mount Bromo is an active volcano located in East Java, Indonesia. It is part of the Tengger massif, and stands at an altitude of 2,329 meters (7,641 feet). The volcano is a popular tourist destination, known for its spectacular views of the surrounding area, including the vast Sand Sea that lies at the base of the mountain. The most common way to reach the mountain is to hike from the nearby village of Cemoro Lawang, although jeep and horseback tours are also available. Climbing to the summit of the volcano is possible, but it is considered a challenging and dangerous hike, and should only be attempted by experienced hikers with proper equipment and guidance.

name: Purwodadi Botanical Garden
address: Jl. Raya Surabaya - Malang No.Km. 65, Sembung Lor, Parerejo, Kec. Purwodadi, Pasuruan, Jawa Timur 67163
description: Purwodadi Botanical Garden is a research centre in Purwodadi, Pasuruan, East Java, Indonesia. It has an area of 85 hectares (210 acres) and more than 10,000 types of trees and many plant collections. The garden was established on January 30, 1941 by Dr. Gerhard Lourens Baas Becking Marinus from the initiative of Dr. Dirk Fok van Slooten as a division of Bogor Botanical Gardens. This garden is one of the three branches of the Botanic Gardens of Indonesia, with each having specific tasks and functions. The two other branches are Cibodas Botanical Garden and Bali Botanic Garden. Management of the entire botanical garden branch is under the responsibility of the Indonesian Institute of Sciences. Initially, the gardens were used for plantation crop research activities. Then in 1954 the basics of a botanic garden began to be applied, with the establishment of patches of plant collections. From 1980 most of the plants were reorganized according to the Engler classification system. Purwodadi is a major centre of research on plant conservation and plants of dry climates in the tropics.

name: Candi Jawi
address: Jl. Raya Candiwates, Jawi, Candi Wates, Kec. Prigen, Pasuruan, Jawa Timur 67157
description: Jawi temple is a syncretic Hindu-Buddhist candi dated from late 13th century Singhasari kingdom. The temple is located on the eastern slope of Mount Welirang, Candi Wates village, Kecamatan Prigen, Pasuruan, East Java, Indonesia, approximately 31 kilometers west of Pasuruan city or 41 kilometers south of Surabaya. The temple located on the main road between Kecamatan Pandaan – Kecamatan Prigen and Pringebukan. The temple was thought to be a Hindu-Buddhist place of worship, however the temple actually was dedicated as mortuary temple to honor King Kertanegara, the last king of Singhasari. It is believed that the ashes of the late king were also placed in two more temples, the Singhasari temple and Jago temple. The Nagarakretagama canto 56 mentioned this temple as Jajawa. King Kertanegara of Singhasari ordered the construction of this temple to provide a place of worship for the adherents of Shiva-Buddha sect, a syncretic religion patronage by the king.

name: Lawang Sewu
address: Jl. Pemuda No.160, Sekayu, Kec. Semarang Tengah, Kota Semarang, Jawa Tengah 50132
description: Lawang Sewu is an office building located opposite Tugu Muda, Semarang City, Central Java, Indonesia, which was built as the head office of the Nederlandsch-Indische Spoorweg Maatschappij (NIS). This building has the status of an Indonesian Railways (KAI) asset because it was the fruit of the struggle for the NIS by the Republic of Indonesia Railways Service (DKARI) during the War of Independence. Currently the building is used as a museum and gallery of railroad history by the Central Unit for Preservation and Architectural Design and KAI Wisata.

name: Saloka Theme Park
address: Jl. Fatmawati No.154, Gumuksari, Lopait, Kec. Tuntang, Kabupaten Semarang, Jawa Tengah 50773
description: Saloka Theme Park or Saloka Park is a thematic amusement park located in Semarang Regency, Central Java. The name Saloka was inspired by the folk legend of Rawa Pening, namely Ki Hajar Salokantara who had a son named Baru Klinthing.

name: Klenteng Sam Poo Kong
address: Jl. Simongan No.129, Bongsari, Kec. Semarang Barat, Kota Semarang, Jawa Tengah 50148
description: The Sam Poo Kong Ancient Building Temple is the former stopover and first landing place for a Muslim Chinese admiral named Zheng He/Cheng Ho, who is also known as Sam Poo (三保). Not all crew members are Muslim. The Sam Poo Kong complex is located in the Simongan area, southwest of Semarang City. The sign indicating that it was a former shrine with Islamic characteristics was found with an inscription reading. Let us observe a moment of silence by listening to the recitation of the Qur'an

name: Kota Lama Semarang
address: Jl. Letjen Suprapto No.31, Tj. Mas, Kec. Semarang Utara, Kota Semarang, Jawa Tengah 50137
description: The Kota Lama Semarang is an area in Semarang which became a trading center in the 19-20 centuries. At that time, to protect the people and their territory, a fort was built in the area, which was named the Vijfhoek fortress. To speed up the transportation routes between the three gates in the fort, transportation roads were made, with the main road being named Heerenstraat. Currently named Jl. Lt. Gen. Soeprapto. One of the locations of the fort's gate that exists today is the Berok Bridge, which is called De Zuider Por. The word 'Berok' itself is the result of the pronunciation of Indigenous people who have difficulty pronouncing the word 'Burg' in Dutch.

name: Pagoda Avalokitesvara
address: Jl. Perintis Kemerdekaan, Pudakpayung, Kec. Banyumanik, Kota Semarang, Jawa Tengah 50265
description: Buddhagaya Watugong Temple or also known as the Buddhagaya Temple is a Buddhist place of worship located in Pudakpayung, Banyumanik, Semarang, Central Java. The exact location is in front of the Kodam IV/Diponegoro Headquarters. The Buddhist Gaya Watugong Temple complex consists of two main main buildings, namely the Avalokitesvara and Dhammasala Pagodas as well as several other buildings. Avalokitesvara Pagoda is a building that has high artistic value, with a height of up to 45 meters and is designated as the tallest pagoda in Indonesia. Inside there is a statue of Dewi Kwan Im with a height of five meters. Meanwhile, Dhammasala consists of two floors where the ground floor is used as a multipurpose hall for meeting activities and the upper floor is used for religious ceremonies where there is a statue of the Buddha.

name: Museum Ranggawarsita
address: Jl. Abdulrahman Saleh No.1, Kalibanteng Kidul, Kec. Semarang Barat, Kota Semarang, Jawa Tengah 50149
description: The Ranggawarsita Central Java Museum is a museum that stores and exhibits various cultural heritages and cultural objects of Central Java which are located in the city of Semarang, Indonesia. This museum was inaugurated on July 5, 1989 and has a collection of 59,784 collections

name: Brown Canyon Semarang
address: Rowosari, Kec. Tembalang, Kota Semarang, Jawa Tengah
description: In Indonesia, Brown Canyon is a former mining land in Meteseh, Tembalang, Semarang.[1][2] This location is one of the popular locations (not a tourist spot) in Semarang and is considered similar to the Grand Canyon in the United States. This similarity lies in the hills that turn into steep cliffs

name: Umbul Sidomukti

description: Umbul Sidomukti is a mountainous natural tourist object located in Sidomukti Village, Bandungan District, Semarang Regency, Central Java. Umbul Sidomukti is located on the slopes of Mount Ungaran with an altitude of 1200 meters above sea level. As a result, Umbul Sidomukti has cool air with stunning natural scenery. This area can be a vacation agenda with family.

name: Ayanaz Gedong Songo
address: Candi Gedong Songo, Krajan, Banyukuning, Bandungan, Kabupaten Semarang, Jawa Tengah 50614
description: Ayanaz Gedongsongo is a tourist attraction with a variety of contemporary spots, and Gedong Songo Temple, which incidentally is a historical tourist attraction in one area, presents a collaboration combining two tourism themes. Ancient tourism themes as evidenced by the presence of Gedong Songo Temple, as well as tours with contemporary themes marked by the presence of Ayanaz Gedong Songo

name: Taman Bunga Celosia
address: Jl. Ke Candi Gedong Songo No.KM, RW.5, Beroken, Candi, Bandungan, Kabupaten Semarang, Jawa Tengah 50614
description: Taman Bunga Celosia merupakan destinasi wisata di lereng kaki gunung Ungaran, Bandungan Kabupaten Semarang. Pemandangan sekitar khas pegunungan, ditambah dengan iklim yang sejuk membuat wisatawan berkunjung ke Taman Bunga Celosia. Taman Bunga Celosia didirikan oleh seorang pelopor muda pertanian tahun 2017. Taman Bunga Celosia dibangun dengan konsep kekinian taman bunga, spot foto, wahana permainan dan cafe garden (kuliner). Wisata ini cocok untuk semua usia mulai dari anak, remaja, dewasa, maupun lansia. Terdapat ratusan jenis bunga hias. Melayani penjualan bunga hias dalam bentuk pot yang terletak berdampingan wisata Taman Bunga Celosia

name: The Great Asia Africa

description: The Great Asia Africa is a tourist attraction that presents the charm of the beauty of architecture and culture in Asia and Africa in one region. The presence of The Great Asia Africa is able to fill the tourist thirst of everyone who wants to travel around the world. You don't need to go far, you don't need to spend a lot, just come to The Great Asia Africa Lembang, Bandung.

name: Dago Dream Park
address: Mekarwangi, Jl. Dago Giri No.Km. 2.2, Pagerwangi, Kec. Lembang, Kabupaten Bandung Barat, Jawa Barat 40135
description: Dago Dreampark offers natural beauty from a height accompanied by interesting instagramable rides such as the Aladdin Carpet, Sky Bike and Up House. Also their adventure rides such as ATV, Mini ATV, Fin Komodo, and Flying Fox. Apart from rides, Dago Dreampark also offers a variety of food at various restaurants that can accompany your holiday activities at Dago Dreampark. Among them are Resto De Java, Unicorn Wingz Cafe, and Waroeng Dayang Sumbi. The facilities offered are also fairly complete. Dago Dreampark has a multi-purpose room, a large parking area, and prayer rooms at various points. Dago Dreampark also facilitates other activities such as Pre-Wedding, Gathering and Outbound photos.

name: Orchid Forest Cikole
address: Genteng, Cikole, Kec. Lembang, Kabupaten Bandung Barat, Jawa Barat 40391
description: Established since 2017, Orchid Forest Cikole is a pine cikole natural tourism park with Edu Tourism, Eco Tourism and Sport Tourism products. Orchid Forest Cikole is also listed as one of the Wonderful Indonesia co-brands and is the best nature tourism with the nomadic tourism concept version of the Ministry of Tourism and Creative Economy in 2019. It has more than 150 collections of orchid species originating from various parts of the world, starting from South America, Peru , to Papua. Orchid Forest Cikole has succeeded in bringing in tens of thousands of visitors from within and outside the country with the aim of being exposed to the wealth and natural beauty of Indonesia.

name: Kawah Putih Ciwidey
address: Sugihmukti, Kec. Pasirjambu, Kabupaten Bandung, Jawa Barat
description: Kawah Putih is a tourist spot in West Java which is located in Alam Endah Village, Rancabali District, Bandung Regency, West Java, which is located at the foot of Mount Patuha. White crater is a lake formed from the eruption of Mount Patuha.

name: Lembang Park & Zoo
address: Jl. Kolonel Masturi No.171, Sukajaya, Kec. Lembang, Kabupaten Bandung Barat, Jawa Barat 40391
description: Lembang Park And Zoo is one of the family's favorite places for a vacation while in the flower city of Bandung, West Java. Is one of the newest tourist attractions in Bandung with a zoo treat in which there are more than 500 types of animals. This zoo in Bandung is highly recommended for you to explore with your beloved family on weekends. By witnessing a variety of unique animals and carrying out various interesting tourist activities, you cannot miss Lembang Park Zoo. So if you are in the city of flowers, it is really mandatory to visit Lembang Park And Zoo Bandung. And enjoy a vacation full of impressions by playing, learning as well as interacting with the various animals that exist to make it a special moment.

name: Jendela Alam
address: Komplek Graha Puspa, Jl. Sersan Bajuri No.KM, RW.5, Cihideung, Kec. Parongpong, Kabupaten Bandung Barat, Jawa Barat 40559
description: This active farm and ranch also offers a variety of recreational activities and outbound arenas for children as well as adults. Visitors can see beautiful scenery while enjoying the fresh air at the Lembang Natural Window. These are the best tourist destinations to spend quality time with family or friends. Make sure you take part in various activities including educational tours, such as farming or feeding rabbits, chickens, and ducks at Window of Nature Bandung. There are also activities like harvesting eggs like a real farmer, catching fish, witnessing the process of milking cows, horseback riding, and much more! If you like art, at Jendela Alam Lembang you can hone your artistic spirit by decorating clay, creating natural works of art, or decorating kites. In addition, your little one can also hunt for treasure with their friends. Visitors can also enjoy exciting games like playing the flying fox at Jendela Alam Bandung! Children under 85 cm can enter for free. So, make sure you take your baby with you. No need to worry. Jendela Alam Lembang has implemented health protocols according to government recommendations, really! Before entering the Window of Nature area, visitors will be checked for body temperature. After entering, there are also facilities such as a place to wash hands and hand sanitizers that can be used.

name: Taman Wisata Bougenville
address: Jl. Gn. Puntang, Campakamulya, Kec. Cimaung, Kabupaten Bandung, Jawa Barat 40374
description: Bougenville Tourism Park is a tourist spot with natural nuances that offers lodging with complete facilities. The concept is a tourist area with lodging as well as several tourist areas and natural rides. The beautiful and natural atmosphere at the Bougenville Tourism Park can be seen from the inn building to the well-maintained flower gardens. In addition, the existence of the Cigeureuh River adds to the calm and comfortable atmosphere of this tourist spot for visitors. The location of this tourist spot is on Jalan Gunung Puntang, Campaka Mulya Village, Cimaung District, Banjaran, Bandung Regency, West Java.

name: Saung Angklung Udjo
address: Jl. Padasuka No.118, Pasirlayung, Kec. Cibeunying Kidul, Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat 40192
description: Saung Angklung Udjo is a complete cultural and educational tourism destination, because it has a performance arena, a bamboo craft center and workshops for bamboo musical instruments. Apart from that, the presence of Saung Angklung Udjo in Bandung has become more meaningful because of his concern to continue to preserve and develop Sundanese culture - especially Angklung - to the community through education and training facilities.

name: Tangkuban Perahu
address: Cikahuripan, Kecamatan Lembang, Kabupaten Bandung, Jawa Barat
description: Tangkuban Perahu is a volcano located in West Java, precisely in Lembang, approximately 30 km north of the city of Bandung. Has a height of up to 2,084 meters above sea level. According to history circulating in the community, the name Tangkuban Perahu is very closely related to a very famous Sundanese legend, namely the Legend of Sangkuriang. Mount Tangkuban Perahu looks like an overturned boat from afar, it is said that this was caused by Sangkuriang's supernatural powers, which failed to complete his task of making a boat to marry Dayang Sumbi, who was none other than his own mother.

name: Kebun Bunga Begonia Lembang
address: Jl. Maribaya No.120 A, Langensari, Kec. Lembang, Kabupaten Bandung Barat, Jawa Barat 40391
description: Lembang Begonia Garden is one of the natural recreation areas in Bandung. The diversity of ornamental plants in this tourist garden is unique in attracting tourists. Balinea flowers originating from Bali are the mascots in this garden. Bandung Begonia Garden has many cool photo areas. This makes visitors feel at home for long in this garden. The beautiful garden atmosphere makes this tourist attraction very suitable to be visited with family.

name: Ullen Sentalu Museum
address: Jl. Boyong No.KM 25, Kaliurang, Hargobinangun, Kec. Pakem, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55582
description: The Ullen Sentalu Museum was founded by the Jogja government initiated by the Haryono family and the Ulating Blencong Foundation. The name Ullen Sentalu embedded in this museum stands for a Javanese proverb, namely Ulating Blencong Sejatining Tataraning Lumaku. This philosophy means the flame of a bencong lamp as a guide for mankind in moving forward and pursuing life. The hope is that the existence of this museum can be a reminder of how national identity and culture were instilled by the Mataram kingdom in the past. This museum was completed and inaugurated on March 1, 1997 by KGPAA Paku Alam VIII. Since its inauguration, this tourist destination has started to get crowded and has become one of the famous tourist attractions in Jogja. The location of this museum is above the altitude of the Sleman mountain area with a land area of ​​around 1.2 hectares. Its location on the slopes of Mount Merapi makes this place feel cool with temperatures around 15 to 25 degrees Celsius. In addition, the many trees that grow around the museum area add to the beautiful atmosphere. This museum area is also known as Ndalem Kaswargan or Heaven's House due to its beauty and peaceful atmosphere.
